  <!-- Foster FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-bg">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-12">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer font-semibold">
            Do I need experience to foster?
            <svg width="20" height="20" class="text-text-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Not at all. Our rescue partners provide full guidance and support for every foster. All you need is a safe space, some patience, and a willingness to give a dog a chance. You'll never be on your own.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer font-semibold">
            What if I already have pets at home?
            <svg width="20" height="20" class="text-text-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Many of our fosters have resident pets. We carefully match foster dogs with homes where they'll thrive, and we always do a temperament assessment first. You'll know upfront whether a particular dog is a good fit for your household.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer font-semibold">
            How long is a typical foster placement?
            <svg width="20" height="20" class="text-text-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Most foster placements last 2 to 8 weeks, but we're flexible. Some dogs find their forever home quickly, while others need a bit more time. We also offer short-term "sleepover" fosters for dogs who just need a break from the shelter environment.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer font-semibold">
            What supplies and support are provided?
            <svg width="20" height="20" class="text-text-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Everything your foster dog needs is covered — food, crate, leash, toys, and all veterinary care including vaccinations, spay/neuter, and any emergency treatment. You'll also have a dedicated support contact available whenever you need help or have questions.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
          <summary class="flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer font-semibold">
            Can I adopt my foster dog?
            <svg width="20" height="20" class="text-text-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
            Yes — it's called a "foster fail" and it happens more often than you'd think! If you and your foster dog are a perfect match, our rescue partner can walk you through the adoption process. There's no pressure either way.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

